parameters: If I meet a demon, I'll slap it right in the face.

I'm transporting fish to Tsukiji. The port of Edo is truly a
great fishing ground with an abundance of fish.

The mandarin oranges I got from you were delicious. Thanks a
lot.
Oh! Is that a mandarin orange?
I got it from the mandarin shop, why do you ask?

It's from Kishu, isn't it? Brings back memories. I was born
in Kishu myself. I haven't had one in a while, so if you
don't mind, could you give me that mandarin orange?

Hehe. You're a kind person, aren't you? It doesn't feel
right to just take it for free. Here, I'll give you this
fabric in return.

Yeah. I'm really happy with your kindness. It's not silk,
just a cheaper cotton fabric. So don't hesitate and take it.
Thank you very much! Then I'll take the fabric with me.

--Karin exchanged the mandarin orange and obtained
\c[17]Fabric\c[0]! (Next  Tsukiji)
--Karin got caught up in the sumo wrestlers' practice!

No, no, young lady. You can't just barge in while they're
seriously practicing... You could get seriously injured, you
know?

This bridge was recently completed. It's designed to be high
enough for ships to pass underneath.

The old lady who was always at the railing of that bridge, I
heard she was reunited with her daughter who had gone far
away. She was so happy.

Interested in sumo, are you? I'm glad. Feel free to watch
the practice as much as you like.

(First, let's go to the Fox Tea House in Ueno to meet
Masaki-chan.)

Lately, there have been rumors about encountering demons.
Well, I think it's just a tall tale.

(First, let's go to the Fox Tea House in Ueno to meet
Masaki-chan.)

Come, come, these are fresh vegetables picked first thing in
the morning! Take them in your hands and see for yourself!

All the trash from Edo ends up here. The plan is to reclaim
the land and expand it even further.

A hundred years ago, it seems that everything east of the
castle was all sea. Edo has a history of continuous land
reclamation, huh.

Sis, you're so cute I bet you'd become a top courtesan in
no time if you worked in the pleasure district.

As you can see, it's deserted. Many have evacuated to
Shimousa by boat. I wonder what will become of Edo from now
on...
I'm taking a break right now. Want to have some rice balls?
Trade has stopped and there's nothing to do. What a drag.

No matter how strong a sumo wrestler is, they can't give
their all when injured. There are talented young wrestlers
who have left the stable after spraining an ankle. Sumo
truly is a world where the body is the capital.

The sumo wrestlers are in the middle of practice for the
charity tournament. Make sure to come and watch when we put
on the show.

The stable master told me to eat lots of chanko nabe to get
bigger.
Our place is a bar for the night. Come after it gets dark.
[Notice] The shop turns into a potion store at night--

(A potion store? I wonder what they sell? It's
intriguing...)

[Notice] The shop turns into a secret potion store at
night--

From this dock, the exiled criminals are sent to a distant
island. It's a harsh punishment from which no one returns.

You, have you returned from Mujou Island!? I have business
with you! ...Eh!? You've received pardon from the shogunate?
Hmm, I have absolutely no idea what you're talking about...

Fukagawa may have escaped damage, but with the tales of
demon attacks spreading, more people are leaving Edo. If
this continues, the future looks bleak...

(First, let's go to the Fox Tea House in Ueno to meet with
Masaki-chan.)
Dozing off... (The portly vagabond is napping...)
(What's with this person? They have such a large body...)
(...It's not good to talk to them strangely. Let's go back.)
Hey! You came to see me again? I'm so happy

...I didn't come to talk to you. I just happened to... just
happened to pass by this way, okay?
It's Kuma Haru. Make sure you remember it, okay?

Hehe! Is that so? Wanna play around again? It's convenient
on the boat since no one notices even during the day.
Follow Kuma Haru for a \c[27][H Event]\c[0]
\c[27]Number of times had sex +1, Creampie +1, Lewdness +3\c[0]

I'm sorry, I have other things to do... (It would be
terrible if something bad happened again...)

I'm really sorry about the other day. It was my first time
with a woman, so I got too excited... I didn't mean to make
you faint...

Yeah. I might look older because of my thick beard, but I'm
actually in my early twenties.

Why did you come to see me again? To be honest, I thought
you'd never come back...
Eh... Well, the hotpot last time was delicious...

Yes, really! It's not like I came back because I wanted to
do lewd things! I mean it!

Hehehe! In that case, how about this: I'll treat you to
hotpot if you let me hold you just one more time?

This time I'll be gentle... You're the first person who ever
slept with me.

(What is this feeling? Being called someone's first doesn't
feel bad...)
Nod in agreement to being embraced \c[27][H Event]\c[0]

...Sorry, but I don't come cheap, you know? You won't get to
touch me ever again.
--Karin left the scene with a displeased look on her face.
Hello, Kumaharu. It's nice weather again today.
--Oh, is that you, Karin? I've been waiting for you
Huh? You look refreshed. What happened to your beard?

Ah... I shaved it this morning. Can't go back to the
countryside with a scruffy beard.

Yeah. I'll be leaving Edo soon. I've come to think that it's
not good for me to stay here any longer.

Hehehe, I'm glad to see you looking sad. Since it's the last
time, let me hold you as a farewell gift.
Snuggle up to Kuma Haru \c[10][Vagabond End]\c[0]

...I'm sorry. If we won't see each other again, then let's
not do it today. Take care when you go back to the
countryside...
--Karin left the place with a sad look on her face.

There's a checkpoint up ahead, but the road has caved in and
created a large puddle, so we're currently working on
draining the water. It won't be passable for a while. Sorry
about that.

Really, these poorly drained roads are such a hassle... And
here I am, a courier in a hurry...

This is the prison estate. Even women and children will be
imprisoned if they commit crimes.

(...If I'm not careful, I could end up being confined in
this prison. I must be cautious not to get caught when
stealing.)

Hmm... Could you possibly be...? No... never mind. Make sure
to rehabilitate and live righteously, okay?

Because martial law has been declared, we're on guard duty
without rest. It would be serious trouble if the criminals
took advantage of this disturbance to escape, so we're
working with a sense of tension.

Sorry for the long period of no contact. There's a
checkpoint to the east.

[Sign] Now Recruiting New Disciples! Healthy boys with
strong physiques are highly welcome!
--Huh!? No, you're mistaken! My name is Karin!

Ah... I'm sorry... You just looked so much like my
daughter... I mistook you for her...

Your daughter, what happened to her? From the way you speak,
she hasn't returned home, has she?

Yes... I'm frail and often ill... So my daughter entered the
pleasure district to earn money for expensive medicine...
But she got into a dispute with a violent client and ended
up injuring him. As a criminal, she was exiled from this
bridge's dock to an island two years ago.
Eh!? Your daughter was exiled to an island...?

It's a very distant island. A place called "Mujou Island,"
south of Izu... I may never see her again, but I can't help
but wait here on this bridge for Kachou.
I see... It must be lonely being separated like that.

Karin-san, was it? If you ever meet Kachou, please tell her.
Tell her that her mother is always waiting for her return...
--The old woman looks sad as she gazes at the dock...
